def: Related to, or of the nature of, aërobies; as, aërobioticplants, which live only when supplied with free oxygen.
One of the quinoline bases, obtained from coal tar as an oilyliquid, C11H11N; also, any one of several substances metameric with,and resembling, cryptidine proper.
To take in with the ears; to hear. [Sportive] "I eared herlanguage." Two Noble Kinsmen.
Pertaining to the science or doctrine of refracted sounds.
Whatever person; any person who; be or she who; any one who;as, he shall be punished, whoever he may be. "Whoever envies orrepines." Milton. "Whoever the king favors." Shak.
A man sphinx; a sphinx having the head of a man and the body ofa lion.
Wearing pattens. "Some pattened girl." Jane Austen.
